                <div class="jonra" data-uuid="bd12bd650f9d4622bbec5eb97502cc04">
                    <h2 data-uuid="ce976a28b19d4a02aed62430d7d07862">Fairview Inn on Old Frederick Road</h2>
                    <p class="source" data-uuid="d6c3c7b5cb9c41a7871650ebfad74d90">Artist Thomas Coke Ruckle painted this busy scene of Fairview Inn, or Three Mile House, in about 1829. The inn was only a few miles west of Baltimore, Maryland, on a road that became part of the National Road.</p>
                </div>
